    "3b87d4bb-4c59-4446-8633-65c34afd8927": {
      "type": "product-faq",
      "blocks": {
        "a83dfeba-8390-4c07-9677-bf8b9b89dd6d": {
          "type": "testimonial",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Produced In Aotearoa New Zealand",
            "description": "<p>Produced In Aotearoa New Zealand: all our honey is foraged, harvested, packed, labelled and tested in New Zealand, meaning that what you are receiving is 100% genuine, as stated on the jar.</p>"
          }
        },
        "e73bf960-757b-4872-bdea-076daf1c6ae9": {
          "type": "testimonial",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Pure Monofloral Manuka Honey",
            "description": "<p>Our manuka honey is predominantly foraged by bees from the manuka flower.  As bees make their journeys to and from the hive, they can encounter a number of floral varieties.  This is why we test every batch of our honey, to ensure it contains the natural markers that make manuka honey so sought after. Our manuka honey is an organic, natural living food. This means that it still contains all the natural pollen and enzymes produced by the bees. Made by nature. Every pot is tested for agrichemicals and other impurities. We’re Non-GMO verified, members of the Detox Project, glyphosate residue-free, Kosher and Halal certified.</p>"
          }
        },
        "afe2be0b-9322-45a7-9583-091073cfe919": {
          "type": "testimonial",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Sustainably Curated in Partnership with Nature",
            "description": "<p>Manuka is an indigenous tree of New Zealand that plays an important role in regenerating forests and supporting local ecosystems. Manuka honey can only be sourced from our beautiful country. \n\nApproximately 95% of our packaging comes from recycled materials – with a commitment to improving wherever we can. We currently use 100% recyclable PETE 1 packaging, free from BPA. This is one of the most widely accepted plastics for recycling around the world.  Our card paper is from sustainably managed forests and controlled sources.\n\nWe are continually investigating more sustainable packaging that focuses on a reduction of virgin materials. This is an immediate goal for us. \n\nPlease reuse or recycle in accordance with your local recycling centre processes.</p>"
          }
        },
        "b1c4a778-1496-4df4-a997-e575fcef67fc": {
          "type": "testimonial",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Traceable to the Source",
            "description": "<p>Just scan the QR code on the label to see the UMF™ certificate and find out exactly where in New Zealand it came from!  \n\nAll our manuka honey is tested in independent government-approved laboratories. Your certificate will indicate the UMF™ grading, MGO levels and more.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
